1. Yesterday, the US Bitcoin spot ETF had a net inflow of US$342.08 million;
2. Yesterday, the US Ethereum spot ETF had a net inflow of US$316.53 million;
3. Hester Peirce: The Cryptocurrency Working Group intends to recommend that the SEC take action to provide temporary forward-looking and retroactive relief for token issuance;
4. Bullish, supported by Peter Thiel, plans to IPO this year and is negotiating with Jefferies Group for potential listing;
5. Coinbase Chief Legal Officer urges the SEC to immediately submit documents related to the ETH 2.0 investigation;
6. Berachain Ecosystem Meme Coin Project Henlo Completes US$3 Million Seed Round of Financing, with Framework Ventures and others participating;
7. Report: Bitcoin has achieved a market value of US$850 billion and has become a global macro asset that many countries and institutions are paying attention to;
8. MicroStrategy is recruiting a new director of capital markets to be responsible for equity, convertible debt and preferred stock issuance;
9. David Sacks: Crypto regulation is expected to be completed in the next six months;
10. Stripe completed the $1.1 billion acquisition of Bridge and absorbed its team;
11. Arkham updated Satoshi Nakamoto's holding address, and the current holding value is about $107.46 billion.
